SIMPLE: fingering
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fingering
<hw>Fin"ger*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process
of handling or touching with the fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mere sight and <qex>fingering</qex> of money.</q>
<rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The manner of using the fingers in playing or
striking the keys of an instrument of music; movement or management of
the fingers in playing on a musical instrument, in typewriting,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The marking of the notes of a piece of music to
guide or regulate the action or use of the fingers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Delicate work made with the fingers.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fingerling</ent>⟦br⟧
